<paragraph id="7D0434C34D75ECFC4344C769E1574DB5" pageId="8" pageNumber="171">Comments</paragraph>
<paragraph id="6B317B8C860F4779CE40600FF7A63E40" pageId="8" pageNumber="171">
Found on tree trunks in transitional miombo woodland at lower slopes (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="21ADB57E50A9EBE796C00CC582027293" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. A selection of reptiles from northern Mozambique inselbergs. A - Nadzikambia baylissi (Mt. Namuli, PEM R 21165), B - Rhampholeon tilburyi (Mt. Namuli, PEM R 21157), C - Rhampholeon sp. (Mt. M'paluwe, PEM R 21209), D - Lygodactylus cf. rex (Mt. Mabu, PEM R 21147), E - Holaspis laevis (Mt. Mabu, PEM R 21146), F - Dipsadoboa cf. shrevei shrevei (Mt. Mabu, PEM R 21123), G - Duberria shirana (Mt. Namuli, PEM R 21184), H - Psammophylax variabilis (Mt. Namuli, PEM R 21186)." figureDoi="10.3897/zse.92.9948.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/104230" pageId="8" pageNumber="171">4E</figureCitation>
). This secretive species is only known from Amatongas, in central Mozambique (
<bibRefCitation id="56977391FE66558033A2E9242FA11476" author="Cott, HN" journalOrPublisher="Proceedings of the Zoological Society of London" pageId="10" pageNumber="173" pagination="145 - 173" publicationUrl="10.1111/j.1469-7998.1934.tb06228.x" refId="B34" refString="Cott, HN, 1934. The Zoological Society's expedition to the Zambesi, 1927: No.5. On a collection of lizards, mainly from Portuguese East Africa, with description of new species of Zonurus, Monopeltis and Chirindia. Proceedings of the Zoological Society of London 1934: 145 - 173, DOI: 10.1111/j.1469-7998.1934.tb06228.x" title="The Zoological Society's expedition to the Zambesi, 1927: No. 5. On a collection of lizards, mainly from Portuguese East Africa, with description of new species of Zonurus, Monopeltis and Chirindia." url="10.1111/j.1469-7998.1934.tb06228.x" volume="1934" year="1934">Cotts 1934</bibRefCitation>
) and numerous unpublished records from other localities in Mozambique: Marromeu area (Branch pers. obs. in 
<bibRefCitation id="339E07389434705B9E7A788B33328BDC" author="Branch, WR" editor="Timberlake, JR" journalOrPublisher="Biodiversity Foundation of Africa, Bulawayo" pageId="10" pageNumber="173" pagination="377 - 392" refId="B7" refString="Branch, WR, 2000. Survey of the reptiles and amphibians of the Zambezi Delta. In: Timberlake, JR, Ed., Biodiversity of the Zambezi Basin Wetlands, Consultancy report for IUCN ROSA. Biodiversity Foundation of Africa, Bulawayo: 377 - 392" title="Survey of the reptiles and amphibians of the Zambezi Delta." volumeTitle="Biodiversity of the Zambezi Basin Wetlands, Consultancy report for IUCN ROSA." year="2000">Branch 2000</bibRefCitation>
), Moebase (Branch pers. obs. in 
<bibRefCitation id="1E6FA10139467B4D4B0F959C7E298FDA" author="Branch, WR" editor="Timberlake, JR" journalOrPublisher="Biodiversity Foundation of Africa, Bulawayo" pageId="10" pageNumber="173" pagination="377 - 392" refId="B7" refString="Branch, WR, 2000. Survey of the reptiles and amphibians of the Zambezi Delta. In: Timberlake, JR, Ed., Biodiversity of the Zambezi Basin Wetlands, Consultancy report for IUCN ROSA. Biodiversity Foundation of Africa, Bulawayo: 377 - 392" title="Survey of the reptiles and amphibians of the Zambezi Delta." volumeTitle="Biodiversity of the Zambezi Basin Wetlands, Consultancy report for IUCN ROSA." year="2000">Branch 2000</bibRefCitation>
), Cavalo near Gorongosa Mountain (Broadley pers. obs in 
<bibRefCitation id="1116F368BC53F524AB354801E72CA2C9" author="Branch, WR" editor="Timberlake, JR" journalOrPublisher="Biodiversity Foundation of Africa, Bulawayo" pageId="10" pageNumber="173" pagination="377 - 392" refId="B7" refString="Branch, WR, 2000. Survey of the reptiles and amphibians of the Zambezi Delta. In: Timberlake, JR, Ed., Biodiversity of the Zambezi Basin Wetlands, Consultancy report for IUCN ROSA. Biodiversity Foundation of Africa, Bulawayo: 377 - 392" title="Survey of the reptiles and amphibians of the Zambezi Delta." volumeTitle="Biodiversity of the Zambezi Basin Wetlands, Consultancy report for IUCN ROSA." year="2000">Branch 2000</bibRefCitation>
), Dondo Inhamitanga Forests (Broadley pers. obs. in 
<bibRefCitation id="F13202E024F04E444B0D70320314EA5A" author="Branch, WR" editor="Timberlake, JR" journalOrPublisher="Biodiversity Foundation of Africa, Bulawayo" pageId="10" pageNumber="173" pagination="377 - 392" refId="B7" refString="Branch, WR, 2000. Survey of the reptiles and amphibians of the Zambezi Delta. In: Timberlake, JR, Ed., Biodiversity of the Zambezi Basin Wetlands, Consultancy report for IUCN ROSA. Biodiversity Foundation of Africa, Bulawayo: 377 - 392" title="Survey of the reptiles and amphibians of the Zambezi Delta." volumeTitle="Biodiversity of the Zambezi Basin Wetlands, Consultancy report for IUCN ROSA." year="2000">Branch 2000</bibRefCitation>
), Quiterajo (Conradie pers. obs.), Italthai (Verburgt pers. obs.), and Palma (Verburgt pers. obs.). It has also been recorded from southern Malawi from the Ruo River Gorge (
<bibRefCitation id="81372364EC7261176203C40D4209F1A1" author="Branch, WR" journalOrPublisher="Report for Mount Mulanje Conservation Trust, Blantyre, Malawi" pageId="10" pageNumber="173" refId="B11" refString="Branch, WR, Cunningham, M, 2006. Herpetological survey of Mount Mulanje, Malawi. Report for Mount Mulanje Conservation Trust, Blantyre, Malawi" title="Herpetological survey of Mount Mulanje, Malawi." year="2006">Branch and Cunningham 2006</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
